{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2012}} {{Use South African English|date=May 2012}} '''''Johnston v Leal'''''<ref>1980 (3) SA 927 (A).</ref> is an important case in [[South African contract law]], heard in the Appellate Division on 22 February [[1980 in South Africa|1980]], by Jansen JA, Corbett JA, Miller JA, Van Winsen AJA and Botha AJA, with judgment handed down on 30 May. The case is valuable, ''inter alia'', for its exposition of the [[parole evidence rule]].<ref>Du Plessis ''et al'' 255.</ref>
